    "# Tuples"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "7f6769aa-831d-4201-be52-b620bdbb33d0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. Tuple is similar to List except that the objects in tuple are immutable which means we cannot \n",
    "change the elements of a tuple once assigned. \n",
    "2. When we do not want to change the data over time, tuple is a preferred data type. \n",
    "3. Iterating over the elements of a tuple is faster compared to iterating over a list. "
   ]
  },
  {
